headline.main: Former Nigerian Governor Jailed for Five Years for Corruption
headline.print_headline: Former Nigerian Governor Jailed for Five Years for Corruption

lead_paragraph: Some 30 people died in clashes between ethnic rebels and Myanmar security forces in a restive area along the border with China on Monday, the government said, dealing a blow to leader Aung San Suu Kyi's goal of reaching peace with minorities.
